                    "company": "Unitedworld Institute of Design (a constituent college of Karnavati University)",
                    "description": "At Unitedworld Institute of Design I delivered Computing, a new course including a trial (2020) at Foundation involving 250 students. The proposal (one.zero) is a serious attempt to embed Computer Literacy, Creative Coding and Computational Thinking in an aligned, progressive and all-inclusive program of three years.\n\nMeanwhile, I decided to end my career as I started, that is by exploring Computing solely. I am programming in both Logo and Processing (Turtle Graphics). My Computer (pen up, pen down) Graphics are recursive, self-organizing systems and thus somehow related to the inspiring work of John Henry Holland (1929-2015) and others connected to the Santa Fe Institute in the early (19)80s. In the near future, I hope to explore, develop, and present some more--what I call--\"Dynamic Self Organising Repeat Patterns\".",
