                    "company": "Frostic School of Art (Western Michigan University)",
                    "description": "Round up in Kalamazoo, Michigan, USA, because my contract ended 2013 May 1. From 2011-2013\nI have been teaching four courses during fall and spring semesters at Gwen Frostic School of Art (Western Michigan University [> http://www.wmich.edu/art/home.php]) : Graphic Design for Non Majors (ART 2450), Color for Graphic Design (ART 2500), Typography 3 (ART 3510), and Visual Systems (ART 3600). On top of this load I have been advising and guiding twenty senior students who were working on their individual final Research Projects (ART 4610). \n\nAmerica has been very inspiring to me. Not only did I produce a number of colorful animations, I started to research \u2018The Goethe and Albers Triangles on the World Wide Web\u2019, and shared my interest with Brenda Danilowitz, the conservator of the Josef and Anni Albers Foundation in Bethany (CT), who received my initiative with enthusiasm.",
